    "reviews": [
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2026-04",
        "text": "I cannot recommend Becky enough!!!! We hired her for our destination wedding in Golden, CO. As we were coming from out of state, Becky was kind enough to offer to help with anything needed, including bringing a wooden hanger to photograph my dress!\n\nBecky has such a calming presence and was a huge help before I was to walk down the aisle. She even carried my lip products with her!\n\nMy now husband and I are super awkward when it comes to taking photos, and Becky made it so comfortable for us and the process felt like it went by soooo quickly. I’ve received my previews and am OBSESSED so far. I cannot wait to see the rest!"
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2025-08",
        "text": "We are so grateful to have chosen Becky as our wedding photographer! She made us feel so comfortable in front of the camera, even my husband who isn't a fan of photos. She struck the perfect balance of letting us truly be in the moment while also making sure every important shot was captured.\n\nOn top of her incredible talent, she was such a calming and fun presence throughout the day. She kept us relaxed, guided us effortlessly when we needed direction, and somehow managed to be everywhere at once without ever feeling intrusive. Our families and friends all commented on how wonderful she was.\n\nThe sneak peek photos we've received so far are absolutely stunning. We can’t recommend Becky enough!!"
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2025-10",
        "text": "Becky was the best wedding photographer I could have asked for and I can’t recommend her highly  enough!\nAs someone who is uncomfortable in front of a camera I was initially nervous about my pictures being taken but once Becky arrived she helped me feel not only comfortable in front of the camera but more relaxed about the day in general.\nBecky is such a kind, genuine and calming presence, her passion really shows and I could feel she truly cared about us and wanted to make our day as special as possible.\nShe helped capture amazing candid moments and also helped us navigate posed pictures and make everything an easy and fun process.\nWe met a few times before the wedding and she helped create a timeline and go over specifics of pictures we wanted and people we wanted them with as well as what we were looking for overall.\nShe was more than a photographer and helped us navigate through stress during the chaos of the day while reminding us to take everything in and enjoy ourselves.\nThe pictures are absolutely stunning and everything we could’ve wanted, she is extremely talented in what she does and just an awesome person to be around. Thank you for everything Becky!"
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2022-10",
        "text": "Becky is amazing! From the communication to the day of the wedding, she is everything you need and more. She even helped keep everything in track during the wedding day.\nSometimes having someone take pictures of you is very awkward, but Becky makes you feel at home and makes you laugh! Every picture that we have from her we absolutely love!"
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2022-09",
        "text": "Becky was the perfect wedding photographer! We initially gravitated toward her because she was so encouraging, thoughtful, and had a calming/positive energy about her.\nWe were 100% right to choose Becky. A few particularly awesome things about her:\n-she is helpful with coming up with ideas and making an adjustable plan\n-she is up for anything\n-she is kind and considerate\n-she is organized and punctual\n-she had great time management and was very efficient but she did it with an easy-going attitude (important on a stressful day)\n-she mixed our ideas and her ideas/expertise and created beautiful shots\nWe've received countless compliments on her photos and everyone was raving about her upbeat personality and professionalism. I highly recommend you book her for your next occasion. She is a wonderful person and a wonderful photographer!"
      }
